Whats new in 2.2.0
------------------

* Code and feature purge

* Slight startup performance boost

* New prerequisite: Class::Singleton

* New prerequisite: Getopt::ArgvFile
  * Superior to Config::Tiny
    # Simplifies config file use
    # Allowed to clean up clive code significantly
  * Replaces Config::Tiny (see below)

* Drop: Config::Tiny dependency

* Drop: IO::Pager (previously optional)
  * "clive --cache-dump | less" works just as well

* Change: configuration, cache and recall paths:
  * ~/.config/clive/config -> ~/.cliverc
  * ~/.config/clive/recall -> ~/.clivelast
  * ~/.config/clive/cache  -> ~/.clivecache

* Old configuration file format is now obsolete
  * Related to Config::Tiny -> Getopt::ArgvFile changes
  * Config::Tiny: clive 2.0 - 2.1
     cat >> ~/.config/clive/config
     [http]
     proxy = "http://foo:1234"
     [output]
     savedir = "/home/my/videos"
  * Getopt::ArgvFile: clive 2.2
     cat >> ~/.cliverc
     --proxy="http://foo:1234"
     --savedir="/home/my/videos"

* Fix: cURL error handling
  * Timeout errors were printed as http/0

* Fix: google mp4 support

* Cache changes
  * Disabled if BerkeleyDB module is not found
  * New option prefix (--cache)
  * New options
    # --cache-read
    # --no-cache
  * Rename old options
  * Passive
    # read (no), write (yes)
  * New default path (~/.clivecache)
  * New key order
  * New delimiter ('#')
  * Add new record fields

* Add: --home-dir

* Add: --recall-file

* Add: --cache-file

* Add: ExtUtils::MakeMaker (Makefile.PL)
  * Replaces GNU Makefile

* Change: --filename-format specifiers

* Change: --emit-csv

  Old: page_link, video_link, filename,   file_length_mb, file_length_bytes,
       video_id,  time_stamp, page_title, initial_length, remaining_bytes

  New: page_link, video_link, filename,   file_length_bytes
       video_id,  page_title

  Removed: file_length_mb, time_stamp, initial_length, remaining_bytes

* Change: Do not strip link params (closes debian bug #530659)

* Change: Dashed long options now have multiple aliases
  * e.g.: --output_file | --output-file | --outputfile

* Change: Exit with an error if --format=id is unrecognized

* Rename: short option: -r => -l

* Change: license ISC -> GPLv3
  
* Remove: many old short options
  * Returned to the pool for reuse

* Remove: --savebatch

* Remove: --renew (obsoleted by passive cache)

* Remove: broken youtube login support (incl. the options)
  * --youtube-user
  * --youtube-pass
  * --no-login

* Remove: --clivepass and Expect module dependency (see above)

* Remove: --emit-xml

* Remove: --background

* Remove: --progress
  * Remove: dot progress type

* Remove: --output, --append

* Remove: --paste ("xclip -o | clive" achieves the same)
  * Drop (optional) "Clipboard" module dependency

* Remove: GNU Makefile

* Remove: clive.1 and clive.pod
  * ExtUtils::MakeMaker -> Makefile -> clive.1 (from bin/clive)
